result.reason: Support/how-to question from 2018 about importing custom vCenter CSV into SQL backend; mRemoteNG already supports CSV import in its own format — user can import CSV then switch to SQL storage
result.approach: No code change needed. mRemoteNG already has CsvConnectionsDeserializerMremotengFormat for CSV import and SQL Server backend support. User should export to mRemoteNG CSV format or import into XML then migrate to SQL. Building a generic custom-CSV-to-SQL mapper is out of scope.
